-- Saudi Rabigh Refining to Restart Polyethylene Production Unit After Fire
-- B y   S h a j i   M a t h e w
-- 2010-10-17T05:54:38Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-17/saudi-rabigh-refining-to-restart-polyethylene-production-unit-after-fire.html
Rabigh Refining and Petrochemicals
Co., a joint venture between state-owned Saudi Aramco and
Sumitomo Chemical Co. of Japan, said it will restart a
polyethylene production unit in 24 hours after a small fire
yesterday. The company made the announcement in a statement to
the Saudi bourse today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Shaji Mathew at 
 shajimathew@bloomberg.net  